<span id="freeTextContainer16891129369328782958">I&apos;ve read this book many times over the years and always enjoy it.<br/>The post-apocolyptic life where people are afraid to repeat the past and keep themselves in a simpler, more natural world, where perfection is all. One can banish those with deformities that can be seen but what can one do to protect oneself (and society) from deformities that one cannot see? <br/>The suspense and intrigue carries through to the end. </span>
  <span id="freeText16891129369328782958" style="display:none">I've read this book many times over the years and always enjoy it.<br />The post-apocolyptic life where people are afraid to repeat the past and keep themselves in a simpler, more natural world, where perfection is all. One can banish those with deformities that can be seen but what can one do to protect oneself (and society) from deformities that one cannot see? <br />The suspense and intrigue carries through to the end. </span>
